WEBVTT

00:49.510 --> 00:51.490
I hope that you'd be okay.

00:56.870 --> 00:58.190
I regretted all along

01:00.060 --> 01:02.140
not seeing you before I left.

01:04.260 --> 01:05.570
I won't be able to be with you.

01:06.990 --> 01:08.380
Please

01:11.039 --> 01:12.050
take care of yourself.

01:12.789 --> 01:14.430
You too, Captain.

01:59.530 --> 02:00.950
This is the Taebaek Unit rescue team!

02:01.830 --> 02:04.110
Is anyone in there?

02:04.110 --> 02:06.190
If you can hear me, knock three times.

02:18.090 --> 02:19.610
I think I was wrong.

02:21.670 --> 02:22.900
No.

02:24.030 --> 02:26.310
If the people who were working at the tower

02:26.310 --> 02:27.750
tried to escape through the east stairs.

02:28.980 --> 02:30.329
Then here is the rescue site.

02:31.000 --> 02:32.440
We've finished cutting the gas pipe.

02:33.370 --> 02:34.650
How's the situation there?

02:36.240 --> 02:39.050
That place is way better than here.

02:39.050 --> 02:40.660
The building is still intact

02:41.350 --> 02:42.460
and there are fewer obstacles

02:42.460 --> 02:44.190
blocking the entrance than here.

02:44.190 --> 02:45.250
Let's go there first.

02:45.250 --> 02:46.630
No.

02:46.630 --> 02:48.310
Debris keeps falling.

02:48.310 --> 02:49.910
Don't be silly.

02:50.260 --> 02:52.350
It's just a few pebbles falling.

02:52.760 --> 02:55.370
If you're that afraid,

02:56.130 --> 02:57.370
how can you do this job?

02:57.940 --> 03:01.010
After an earthquake, a building that hasn't collapsed is more dangerous.

03:01.360 --> 03:03.220
It looks fine from the outside,

03:03.220 --> 03:04.580
but the building has been weakened

03:04.580 --> 03:06.520
by the shock of the earthquake.

03:14.020 --> 03:15.700
Even weak vibrations

03:15.700 --> 03:16.750
from the equipment

03:16.750 --> 03:18.660
can cause more damage.

03:19.940 --> 03:20.660
I hear something.

03:21.550 --> 03:25.230
It's weak, but I can definitely hear something.

03:32.510 --> 03:33.930
Get the endoscope ready

03:33.930 --> 03:35.230
and look inside.

03:35.230 --> 03:36.040
Yes, sir!

03:45.610 --> 03:50.530
Hey! Is that the best you can do?

03:50.530 --> 03:53.070
Hit it harder! Harder!

03:53.410 --> 03:57.810
It hurts. Quickly! Quickly!

03:58.040 --> 04:01.760
Safety first! Safety first!

04:01.760 --> 04:07.210
I know. Safety first. I'm so sorry.

04:07.210 --> 04:09.970
I thought I built it strong.

04:10.400 --> 04:13.140
I didn't know an earthquake would hit us.

04:14.290 --> 04:19.350
They're looking for us.

04:19.350 --> 04:21.959
- Did you hear that? - Did you?

04:21.959 --> 04:23.890
Hear it?

04:23.890 --> 04:25.690
- I think there's someone down there. - Who is it?

04:26.370 --> 04:28.290
- Who is it? - Are you the rescue team?

04:28.590 --> 04:30.130
Is that Mr. Koh?

04:30.450 --> 04:32.350
Mr. Koh, I’m Mr. Park.

04:32.350 --> 04:33.220
Mr. Park!

04:33.220 --> 04:34.870
- Mr. Koh! - Where are you?

04:34.870 --> 04:37.520
I think we're right above you.

04:37.520 --> 04:39.270
Please hang in there.

04:39.270 --> 04:42.130
The rescue team is working hard.

04:42.650 --> 04:45.590
Here! Over here! We're over here.

04:46.040 --> 04:47.530
Please hurry up.

04:47.980 --> 04:51.370
There are lots of casualties. Hurry up!

04:52.010 --> 04:53.450
It's vital to lift the concrete chunks

04:53.450 --> 04:56.230
that are blocking the entrance.

04:56.580 --> 04:58.300
The pulley isn't strong enough to take the weight.

04:58.860 --> 05:00.100
We need to dig through with a drill.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.130
That's not going to work.

05:02.130 --> 05:05.540
This is a fortified concrete wall.

05:05.540 --> 05:06.700
If you want to drill through it,

05:06.700 --> 05:08.040
it'll take more than three days.

05:08.370 --> 05:09.540
We have to find another way.

05:09.540 --> 05:10.800
We have an easy way.

05:10.800 --> 05:12.490
Why do you need another way?

05:12.490 --> 05:14.250
Let's start using heavy machinery.

05:14.250 --> 05:15.340
The ground is weak.

05:15.340 --> 05:17.570
It's dangerous for the people under the ruins

05:17.570 --> 05:19.000
if we use heavy machinery.

05:19.980 --> 05:21.820
What about here? Right here?

05:21.820 --> 05:24.580
Isn't the office building safe?

05:25.330 --> 05:28.700
There are no signs of survivors there.

05:28.700 --> 05:31.570
Let's start with something you can do.

05:31.570 --> 05:33.150
I have very important documents in my office.

05:33.150 --> 05:35.060
Are you suggesting that we should secure

05:35.280 --> 05:37.330
some papers while people are dying?

05:37.330 --> 05:40.840
Hey! Let's get the facts straight here.

05:40.840 --> 05:42.909
The person in charge of this site is me.

05:42.909 --> 05:46.310
I’m the General Manager of the Uruk Power Plant.

05:46.720 --> 05:49.550
That means you should follow my orders...

05:49.550 --> 05:51.100
In disaster areas,

05:51.100 --> 05:52.980
the commander of the rescue team is in charge of the situation,

05:53.630 --> 05:54.640
and I'm the commander.

05:59.880 --> 06:01.420
What idiot let a civilian

06:01.420 --> 06:02.470
into a rescue site?

06:02.850 --> 06:03.760
Hey! You!

06:03.760 --> 06:04.960
Please leave the site.

06:05.250 --> 06:06.510
Get off me.

06:06.510 --> 06:07.700
- How dare you treat me like this? - Please out..

06:07.700 --> 06:09.650
- Don't push me! Stop!

06:09.650 --> 06:12.880
You idiot! Hey! Do you hear me?

06:12.880 --> 06:14.790
Let me talk to your superior! You jerk!

06:16.220 --> 06:18.340
Get your hands off of me! Now!

06:19.050 --> 06:19.720
If we can't lift it up,

06:19.720 --> 06:22.530
why don't we push from underneath? With airbags.

06:22.530 --> 06:23.410
That won't work.

06:23.410 --> 06:26.180
An airbag can hold 10 tons at the most.

06:26.180 --> 06:27.570
That's one airbag.

06:27.570 --> 06:29.230
If we distribute the weight to four airbags

06:29.230 --> 06:31.630
and inflate them all at once, it might work.

06:39.270 --> 06:41.450
But we only have one air pump.

06:41.450 --> 06:44.120
It's impossible to put air into four airbags at the same time.

06:44.930 --> 06:46.180
That's the problem.

06:49.550 --> 06:51.170
What if we fill the other three with water?

06:52.780 --> 06:54.690
The fire hydrants weren't destroyed.

06:55.700 --> 07:00.450
We can take care of the waterproof problem. Let's fill the three airbags with water at the same time.

07:00.810 --> 07:01.750
Connection complete!

07:06.120 --> 07:09.530
I know, but the airbags adapted to fill up with water won't last long.

07:09.870 --> 07:11.950
If we secure enough space for us to pass through,

07:11.950 --> 07:14.320
we can install supporting beams and hope for the best.

07:16.770 --> 07:17.690
Let's try it.

07:18.600 --> 07:20.300
We have a plan. Let's hurry up!

07:20.300 --> 07:21.290
Yes, sir!

07:38.830 --> 07:40.090
I think it's an intestinal perforation.

07:40.460 --> 07:41.770
If we don't treat it, it'll turn into peritonitis.

07:41.770 --> 07:42.880
Send him to the Medical Zone.

07:42.880 --> 07:44.010
We have no vehicles.

07:44.490 --> 07:46.230
Car Three is broken and is being fixed.

07:46.230 --> 07:47.620
We only have Car Two.

07:47.950 --> 07:48.900
This is crazy.

07:49.290 --> 07:50.360
The phones still aren't working?

07:50.670 --> 07:51.490
No.

07:52.060 --> 07:55.820
Doc! Doc! Use this! Here!

07:55.820 --> 07:56.920
Where did you get this?

07:56.920 --> 07:58.820
You know that foreign doctor?

07:58.820 --> 08:00.740
He came to the Medical Zone with a patient.

08:00.740 --> 08:03.630
He said an entire village near the town has disappeared.

08:03.960 --> 08:05.700
He gave them to me.

08:05.700 --> 08:07.920
You can use Channel Three, the army channel.

08:08.860 --> 08:10.250
Dr. Kang, do you copy?

08:10.980 --> 08:13.330
Daniel? Thank you for the walkie-talkies.

08:13.330 --> 08:14.410
Thank you.

08:15.360 --> 08:16.630
Nurse! Nurse!

08:16.630 --> 08:18.590
Can you give me permission to use the OR?

08:18.590 --> 08:20.390
I have a patient with massive bleeding and a fractured skull,

08:20.390 --> 08:22.410
but they won't let me use the OR without your permission.

08:22.410 --> 08:23.450
And I don’t have the permission of his guardian.

08:23.450 --> 08:25.990
I'm about to do the surgery in front of door.

08:26.670 --> 08:28.240
You could get sued for this.

08:28.240 --> 08:31.720
Is the medical director there? Can you hear me?

08:32.049 --> 08:34.049
Why? He didn't make a reservation?

08:34.470 --> 08:35.960
We're not in Seoul.

08:37.179 --> 08:38.240
I'm opening it.

08:41.110 --> 08:42.370
It's open. Thank you.

08:44.790 --> 08:48.830
Make sure you save his life so he can sue you after he gets better.

08:48.830 --> 08:50.420
Roger! Ye Hwa is on her way.

08:50.420 --> 08:51.570
She can help you.

08:51.570 --> 08:54.390
I can use all the help I can get. Thank you. Over!

09:15.890 --> 09:19.040
Who'd go in there

09:19.040 --> 09:22.730
putting faith in airbags

09:24.090 --> 09:25.880
that could burst at any time?

09:25.880 --> 09:28.180
No a normal person would do that.

09:29.760 --> 09:31.220
We do.

09:32.140 --> 09:33.690
The airbags are in place.

10:05.380 --> 10:06.400
Situation room! Situation room!

10:06.890 --> 10:08.690
We have secured a path underground.

10:09.550 --> 10:11.890
Let's start searching.

10:12.650 --> 10:14.110
Send the medical services team over here.

10:27.040 --> 10:29.030
There they are. There they are.

10:30.450 --> 10:31.720
We survive.

10:42.640 --> 10:44.170
This way!

10:47.470 --> 10:49.180
Sir, what's your name?

10:49.180 --> 10:52.430
I'm Park Young Man. Park Young Man.

10:52.430 --> 10:55.090
I'm okay. I don't know

10:55.090 --> 10:57.150
exactly where I was.

10:58.110 --> 10:59.460
But Mr. Koh was under

11:01.110 --> 11:03.540
We're searching the area.

11:04.620 --> 11:05.960
Don't worry.

11:24.690 --> 11:26.720
BP 60 over 30. Drowsy mentality.

11:26.720 --> 11:28.060
Put him on an IV.

11:30.720 --> 11:31.620
We're out.

11:32.760 --> 11:33.520
Here.

11:33.780 --> 11:34.630
Thank you.

11:38.080 --> 11:39.020
Intraperitoneal bleeding?

11:39.020 --> 11:40.830
Abdominal distention and weak pulse.

11:45.570 --> 11:47.390
No vitals. Epinephrine 10 milligrams.

12:07.160 --> 12:08.310
His pulses resume!

12:09.390 --> 12:11.610
It's shock caused by intraperitoneal bleeding.

12:11.610 --> 12:13.880
I should perform a celiotomy. Please get him ready to send him to the Medical Zone.

12:14.380 --> 12:16.080
There's no OR there.

12:16.080 --> 12:17.310
How far is headquarters from here?

12:17.310 --> 12:19.480
At least half an hour by chopper.

12:19.530 --> 12:21.090
He won't last that long.

12:21.090 --> 12:22.200
You have to do it here, then.

12:23.640 --> 12:24.990
Do what?

12:25.320 --> 12:26.720
His pulse is irregular.

12:27.300 --> 12:28.420
Operation.

12:28.880 --> 12:30.120
Not right here.

12:31.200 --> 12:32.790
Over there where the sun is.

12:32.790 --> 12:33.850
It's too dark here.

12:33.850 --> 12:34.770
Are you crazy?

12:34.770 --> 12:36.650
How can I perform surgery without a CT scan?

12:36.650 --> 12:38.230
I don't know where he's bleeding.

12:38.230 --> 12:39.860
That's why you open him up and check.

12:40.030 --> 12:42.130
Does he have any other options?

12:43.420 --> 12:44.630
You want me to open his stomach

12:44.630 --> 12:46.360
in this dusty construction site?

12:46.990 --> 12:49.060
Do you know how many side effects there may be?

12:49.060 --> 12:50.310
Septicemia, fat embolism,

12:50.310 --> 12:51.360
renal insufficiency, cardiac stenosis...

12:51.360 --> 12:53.150
Does he have any other options? Decide quickly.

12:54.660 --> 12:56.530
He's your patient.

12:59.660 --> 13:00.820
This is crazy.

13:04.250 --> 13:05.530
Get me a set of surgical instruments.

13:06.200 --> 13:08.170
Get some betadine and lots of sterilization drapes.

13:08.430 --> 13:09.100
Yes, ma'am.

13:12.150 --> 13:13.780
We need to get him out in the sun.

13:17.570 --> 13:20.250
Ye Hwa! Can you help us here?

13:22.090 --> 13:24.110
Doc! Doc! Use Channel Three.

13:24.110 --> 13:25.090
Thank you.

13:26.390 --> 13:27.570
Doc! Doc! Here!

13:29.910 --> 13:32.130
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

13:32.440 --> 13:33.370
I'm so sorry.

13:34.090 --> 13:34.890
Whatever.

13:35.070 --> 13:37.810
If you're hurt, stay away. I can do it.

13:37.810 --> 13:39.240
I'm sorry.

13:39.620 --> 13:42.190
Get me a set of surgical instruments and betadine.

13:43.600 --> 13:45.090
Was there an aftershock?

13:45.090 --> 13:47.620
No. It was my fault.

13:47.670 --> 13:49.690
What do you need? Vitamins?

13:50.680 --> 13:51.680
Betadine? How much?

13:52.150 --> 13:53.070
As much as you have.

13:53.440 --> 13:55.230
Can I take those sterilization drapes there?

13:55.230 --> 13:56.220
Excuse me.

14:08.730 --> 14:10.360
Let's stop here.

14:12.470 --> 14:13.940
I'll take care of her.

14:35.600 --> 14:36.970
Anesthetic.

14:42.520 --> 14:43.620
So frustrating!

14:45.330 --> 14:47.070
Are you afraid of shots?

14:48.440 --> 14:49.700
Aren’t you in a great deal of pain?

14:50.970 --> 14:52.340
If only she can speak English.

14:55.510 --> 14:58.600
Anesthetic.

14:58.600 --> 14:59.760
It won’t hurt.

15:02.930 --> 15:03.820
Let go!

15:04.220 --> 15:05.490
Ah.

15:08.680 --> 15:09.810
Unbelievable!

15:10.050 --> 15:12.470
No. No Anesthetic.

15:12.640 --> 15:14.270
I’m pregnant. The baby may get hurt.

15:14.270 --> 15:16.980
What’re you saying? What do you want me to do?

15:28.140 --> 15:30.000
Baby.

15:33.370 --> 15:37.520
Pregnant? Baby?

15:43.260 --> 15:46.960
I can’t do the anesthetic. I can’t.

15:47.460 --> 15:50.110
Just do it.

15:51.500 --> 15:53.160
This is crazy.

15:57.970 --> 15:59.390
It'll hurt like crazy.

16:02.000 --> 16:05.260
Can you handle it? Okay?

16:09.210 --> 16:10.530
Okay.

16:17.480 --> 16:25.400
Then let’s begin. One, two, three.

16:46.380 --> 16:48.380
Dr. Kim! Dr. Kim!

16:54.100 --> 16:56.400
Hi, I'm Martin from The World Times.

16:56.400 --> 16:58.650
Is this the casualty count?

16:59.270 --> 17:00.780
My name is Ki Bum.

17:00.780 --> 17:03.900
Ah, yes. You're with the Korean army, right?

17:04.730 --> 17:06.650
Can you fill me in on the situation?

17:07.490 --> 17:09.109
What should I tell him?

17:09.740 --> 17:13.880
I'm a soldier. OK?

17:14.280 --> 17:19.329
Ms. Ha. Ms. Ha. She’s the doctor. No.

17:20.020 --> 17:21.369
Nightingale! Nightingale!

17:21.369 --> 17:22.510
Come on! Come on!

17:23.800 --> 17:25.250
He's an American.

17:25.250 --> 17:27.770
Are you a nurse? May I ask you a couple of things?

17:27.770 --> 17:29.020
I'm busy.

17:35.390 --> 17:36.250
Dr. Song.

17:36.570 --> 17:37.410
He is a doctor.

17:37.410 --> 17:38.290
Come on! Come on!

17:39.700 --> 17:41.010
He's an American.

17:41.010 --> 17:43.860
What's the latest situation? The casualty count is...

17:43.860 --> 17:45.260
I'm not good at English.

17:45.260 --> 17:47.530
So, I beg your pardon.

17:48.930 --> 17:49.890
This is the Medical Zone.

17:49.890 --> 17:51.970
Are there any available doctors at the moment?

17:51.970 --> 17:53.390
We need hands in the OR.

17:54.310 --> 17:56.070
I'm Dr. Song. I'm on my way.

17:56.070 --> 17:57.580
Thank you. Please hurry.

17:57.580 --> 17:58.430
Okay. Over.

18:06.030 --> 18:08.470
Hey! I'll do the interview

18:08.470 --> 18:10.220
if you take me to the hospital.

18:10.520 --> 18:11.880
Come on! Hurry!

18:13.960 --> 18:14.770
Okay.

18:22.230 --> 18:24.200
Wow! He's cool.

18:24.780 --> 18:26.270
He goofs around a lot,

18:26.270 --> 18:27.530
but he's a good doctor.

18:30.210 --> 18:32.590
Attention! AB positive blood is needed!

18:32.590 --> 18:35.130
This is an emergency! Respond if you can donate.

18:35.620 --> 18:37.970
This is Private Kim Ki Bum, a signalman.

18:37.970 --> 18:39.300
I'm AB positive.

18:41.360 --> 18:42.970
Can you clean here? I can't see.

18:44.280 --> 18:45.630
Hold this with a retractor.

18:46.630 --> 18:47.580
He's AB positive.

18:48.030 --> 18:49.730
I'll draw blood. It'll sting.

18:54.840 --> 18:55.570
Dr. Kang.

18:56.710 --> 18:57.780
Are you hurt?

18:57.780 --> 18:58.810
Not me.

18:59.020 --> 19:00.380
We need a doctor in there. Hurry.

19:01.060 --> 19:02.220
This is an emergency.

19:07.810 --> 19:08.720
Mr. Koh!

19:12.110 --> 19:13.650
You're here. Doctor.

19:14.360 --> 19:16.590
It's dangerous in here.

19:16.590 --> 19:17.930
I'll give you some sedatives first.

19:22.160 --> 19:24.900
Can you feel the lower part of your body, like your legs and toes?

19:26.000 --> 19:27.710
I'm an old man.

19:27.710 --> 19:30.390
I don't have much energy.

19:36.070 --> 19:38.270
It's moving, right?

19:41.400 --> 19:44.830
It hurt so much.

19:44.830 --> 19:49.190
I see your face now and I don't feel any pain.

19:49.600 --> 19:51.600
Right. You did well.

19:54.690 --> 19:56.600
How long will it take to lift this thing up?

19:57.400 --> 20:00.910
You have another patient to see.

20:02.820 --> 20:06.520
It hurts! Quickly! Quickly!

20:06.520 --> 20:08.040
Don't move.

20:08.040 --> 20:09.710
You’re lucky it’s not to your heart.

20:09.710 --> 20:12.880
But if you move, it might hit your spine.

20:13.430 --> 20:15.640
Am I going to die?

20:15.640 --> 20:18.650
Try to stay still. You don't die.

20:20.650 --> 20:21.890
We have to cut the steel frame

20:21.890 --> 20:24.030
and move him to the OR with the shard.

20:25.590 --> 20:26.810
Can you cut it right about here?

20:27.770 --> 20:30.030
We need to talk first.

20:30.850 --> 20:32.010
Go ahead.

20:32.510 --> 20:33.690
Just the two of us.

20:44.450 --> 20:45.770
Is there a problem?

20:47.180 --> 20:48.410
The problem is

20:48.410 --> 20:50.150
the two situations are connected to each other.

21:04.260 --> 21:07.020
If we lift the concrete chunk on Mr. Koh's side,

21:07.020 --> 21:08.940
it'll curve the frame as well...

21:13.490 --> 21:15.450
and cut the other guy's body in half.

21:16.240 --> 21:18.340
What if we cut the frame first?

21:19.530 --> 21:22.130
Then the structure's center will shift

21:23.280 --> 21:26.340
and put a tremendous amount of weight on the concrete chunk on Mr. Koh.

21:29.030 --> 21:30.750
Are you saying that if we save one,

21:31.640 --> 21:34.830
the other's going to die?

21:37.560 --> 21:39.320
From an engineering viewpoint, there's no other option.

21:39.320 --> 21:41.090
There's no option medically, either.

21:41.090 --> 21:41.740
In this case,

21:41.740 --> 21:43.960
we have to follow the rescue guidelines.

21:45.060 --> 21:49.270
The doctor will decide to save the one with the highest chance of survival.

21:50.100 --> 21:53.660
Are you telling me that I should decide?

21:54.020 --> 21:56.490
Whom I should save between the two?

21:57.040 --> 21:58.060
Yes.

21:58.760 --> 22:03.020
That's what you should do at the moment.

22:15.350 --> 22:18.140
Either way, we're ready to start working.

22:18.140 --> 22:19.610
It'll take 10 minutes.

22:24.280 --> 22:25.280
Have you made up your mind?

22:25.590 --> 22:26.890
Give me 10 more minutes.

22:26.890 --> 22:27.960
We don't have time.

22:33.620 --> 22:34.590
Okay.

22:44.240 --> 22:46.580
She requested help as a doctor.

22:47.610 --> 22:48.670
Go get ready.

22:49.030 --> 22:49.740
Yes, sir!

22:56.480 --> 22:58.280
What the... Captain Yoo,

22:58.440 --> 23:03.720
you haven't even started yet? This is so frustrating.

23:04.440 --> 23:07.440
You can only save one of the two.

23:08.310 --> 23:11.760
Why don't you choose the easy one,

23:11.760 --> 23:13.510
and go dig up my office, okay?

23:15.370 --> 23:16.790
We're following rescue guidelines.

23:17.200 --> 23:19.510
Where are you going? I'm not done talking.

23:21.860 --> 23:23.810
Do you know what the document is?

23:24.360 --> 23:26.100
It's an agreement

23:26.100 --> 23:27.450
between Korea and Uruk

23:27.450 --> 23:29.340
about the peace reconstruction business.

23:30.280 --> 23:32.880
Even though I get paid by the Uruk government,

23:32.880 --> 23:34.250
I'm still a citizen of the republic of Korea.

23:34.250 --> 23:35.850
I'm telling you this out of patriotism.

23:37.000 --> 23:37.720
When I go to karaoke,

23:37.720 --> 23:40.470
I always sing the Korean national anthem first.

23:40.470 --> 23:41.650
Do you know what I'm saying?

23:41.650 --> 23:44.100
I'm trying to do something good for our country.

23:46.010 --> 23:46.960
What's a soldier's job?

23:48.390 --> 23:50.930
Soldiers put the national interest first in every occasion.

23:51.570 --> 23:52.550
The lives of a couple of labor workers

23:52.550 --> 23:55.030
aren't significant at the moment.

23:55.030 --> 23:56.050
Hey.

23:57.140 --> 23:59.550
Hey? Are you talking to me?

23:59.550 --> 24:01.530
Yes, I'm talking to you, scumbag.

24:03.950 --> 24:05.030
Nation?

24:05.940 --> 24:07.020
What is a nation?

24:07.760 --> 24:10.580
A nation is responsible for the people's lives and safety.

24:10.770 --> 24:12.330
In other words,

24:13.650 --> 24:15.730
even if a jerk like you is in danger,

24:15.730 --> 24:19.210
the nation has to save you using with every efforts.

24:19.210 --> 24:21.130
As a soldier,

24:21.460 --> 24:24.850
saving peoples' lives is the most important mission given by my nation.

24:26.920 --> 24:28.810
If you want that document so badly,

24:36.940 --> 24:38.080
go dig it out yourself.

24:41.270 --> 24:42.490
Unbelievable!

24:46.050 --> 24:47.750
You're making a big mistake now.

24:47.750 --> 24:48.700
I don't care.

24:50.240 --> 24:50.990
Get out!

24:54.860 --> 24:56.180
Heads up!

25:18.090 --> 25:19.080
Is everyone okay?

25:19.870 --> 25:21.610
We're okay here.

25:22.590 --> 25:23.940
Over there!

25:40.720 --> 25:41.620
Are you okay?

25:44.230 --> 25:48.830
Well... I'm okay.

25:49.730 --> 25:50.560
Sergeant Gong,

25:51.150 --> 25:52.660
there are live wires down here.

25:52.660 --> 25:53.890
Can you check into it?

25:53.890 --> 25:54.980
Yes, sir!

26:19.290 --> 26:20.880
The rescue work begins.

26:20.880 --> 26:22.750
When they try to lift the concrete chunk off of you,

26:22.750 --> 26:24.440
it'll hurt a lot for a short period of time.

26:25.110 --> 26:26.390
No painkiller would be effective.

26:26.390 --> 26:30.040
I have three kids. Two girls and a boy.

26:30.620 --> 26:31.390
What?

26:31.880 --> 26:33.460
I'm talking about Bayu.

26:34.010 --> 26:36.200
I guess

26:36.200 --> 26:37.950
you won't be able to save both of us.

26:43.460 --> 26:44.730
I'm okay.

26:45.100 --> 26:48.550
I've worked for 30 years abroad

26:48.550 --> 26:52.170
since we made a highway in the desert of Saudi Arabia.

26:52.490 --> 26:54.070
I know what's going on.

26:57.190 --> 27:00.490
I'll do my best under any circumstances.

27:01.840 --> 27:05.120
Thank you.

27:09.640 --> 27:13.020
I'm lying here looking at the sky without working.

27:13.020 --> 27:15.110
This is nice.

27:15.840 --> 27:18.110
This is my lucky day.

27:19.960 --> 27:24.470
All of my children finished university.

27:29.350 --> 27:34.530
Can you give me more painkillers? It hurts like crazy.

27:35.710 --> 27:38.200
No more painkillers. You have to go under

27:38.200 --> 27:41.190
anesthesia for your surgery later on.

27:43.070 --> 27:46.720
Clench your fist.

27:52.240 --> 27:53.520
Am I going to live?

27:54.830 --> 27:57.890
Please save me! Please.

27:58.990 --> 28:03.130
I didn't move one bit. I promise.

28:04.960 --> 28:06.080
Good.

28:11.940 --> 28:13.270
I've got to make an incision here.

28:13.720 --> 28:16.070
Three centimeters from here. Right angle.

28:16.070 --> 28:16.710
Yes, ma'am.

28:23.830 --> 28:24.700
When he recovers,

28:24.700 --> 28:25.820
ask him to buy you lunch.

28:26.390 --> 28:27.410
Will he live?

28:27.410 --> 28:28.690
You're going to make him live.

28:29.450 --> 28:30.640
Am I?

28:32.350 --> 28:34.160
Private Kim Ki Bum!

28:35.000 --> 28:37.150
I'm saving someone's life.

28:38.330 --> 28:40.060
Can I tell Sergeant Seo about this?

28:40.360 --> 28:42.800
Wait your turn. I'll talk to him first.

28:53.630 --> 28:55.190
Ye Hwa, we didn't come to Uruk for this.

28:55.190 --> 28:56.580
They didn't come

28:56.580 --> 29:00.430
to Uruk to get hurt, either.

29:00.770 --> 29:02.070
You'll keep your promise?

29:02.070 --> 29:05.010
Of course. It's a blood promise.

29:05.010 --> 29:08.500
A. The head of Haeseong Hospital.

29:08.500 --> 29:11.480
B. The head of Mouru Plant.

29:11.480 --> 29:15.150
C. The head of the Taebaek Unit.

29:15.540 --> 29:16.790
Who do you want to interview?

29:17.270 --> 29:20.210
D. Daniel Spencer.

29:21.360 --> 29:23.740
He wasn't in your options.

29:24.370 --> 29:25.500
It'd be nice to have someone

29:25.500 --> 29:27.720
who's a veteran with disaster scenes.

29:27.720 --> 29:32.920
I know. You guys think that he's so famous and smart,

29:34.790 --> 29:36.280
but it's all about the look.

29:36.280 --> 29:38.870
That's exactly why we want Daniel.

29:38.870 --> 29:42.240
Not only can he talk, but he's also got the look.

29:43.910 --> 29:46.340
Unbelievable! You gossip lvers.

29:55.340 --> 29:56.960
The situation here isn't so good.

29:58.400 --> 30:00.250
There are oxygen tanks for welding.

30:00.250 --> 30:01.690
There's a chance of another explosion.

30:04.320 --> 30:06.980
The ground is weak here. Be careful.

30:07.280 --> 30:07.900
Yes, sir!

30:13.060 --> 30:14.540
Sergeant Seo!

30:14.820 --> 30:16.000
What's going on?

30:16.000 --> 30:18.850
The ground collapsed and Sergeant Seo has disappeared from sight!

30:19.230 --> 30:20.970
Did something bad happen to Sergeant Seo?

30:20.970 --> 30:22.180
Can I take this thing out?

30:22.180 --> 30:22.930
Private Kim! Sit down!

30:22.930 --> 30:23.460
But...

30:23.460 --> 30:25.080
Sit down! Are you going to kill him?

30:30.380 --> 30:31.480
Three zero thread.

30:31.700 --> 30:33.160
Yes, ma'am.

30:43.080 --> 30:44.180
This is Wolf.

30:44.540 --> 30:48.130
I fell on the sand, so I didn't get hurt. I'm okay.

30:48.420 --> 30:51.300
Thank god. I think Sergeant Seo is okay.

30:51.300 --> 30:53.380
Stop talking. I can't focus.

31:04.750 --> 31:06.160
We've gotten ready.

31:07.950 --> 31:11.140
Have you made up your mind?

31:12.110 --> 31:15.730
Mr. Koh's leg muscles have started to atrophy.

31:16.690 --> 31:18.760
If we lift the chunk that's pressing down on him,

31:18.760 --> 31:20.580
he'll likely suffer from crush syndrome.

31:22.580 --> 31:23.940
The shard that's penetrating the employee’s body

31:24.670 --> 31:27.420
is stopping him from bleeding too much.

31:27.960 --> 31:29.290
Even if we move him to the OR,

31:29.290 --> 31:31.530
it might be hard to stop the massive hemorrhage.

31:34.690 --> 31:36.560
If you were me,

31:38.680 --> 31:39.740
whom would you save?

31:44.950 --> 31:46.700
Why are you asking me that question?

31:47.660 --> 31:50.300
You saw them and diagnosed them.

31:51.800 --> 31:53.300
Now you have to decide and let me know.

31:54.640 --> 31:55.910
I know.

31:56.360 --> 31:58.760
But you're a lot more experienced than me.

31:59.420 --> 32:01.560
I thought you could choose the best option.

32:01.560 --> 32:04.100
The best option? Do you think

32:04.100 --> 32:06.480
I'm choosing the best option here?

32:08.670 --> 32:10.310
There's no best option on a rescue site like this.

32:11.790 --> 32:13.240
We just solve problems

32:14.020 --> 32:15.370
as we go along.

32:15.670 --> 32:17.070
I know that, but...

32:17.960 --> 32:19.470
Without any systems or orders,

32:19.470 --> 32:21.230
I've seen patients all day.

32:21.230 --> 32:22.510
I don't know if what I'm doing is right and...

32:22.510 --> 32:23.380
You're doing just fine.

32:24.710 --> 32:27.220
In situations like this, you do anything you can

32:27.550 --> 32:29.120
or let people die without doing anything.

32:29.680 --> 32:31.350
Those are the two options you have.

32:32.150 --> 32:33.860
You have no time to hesitate.

32:36.340 --> 32:38.280
We're not asking you to do

32:38.280 --> 32:38.940
a perfect and flawless

32:38.940 --> 32:40.540
job here.

32:41.120 --> 32:45.250
Doctors can't even find the proper treatment for a simple cold sometimes.

32:46.920 --> 32:49.240
We just need you to diagnose patients

32:49.240 --> 32:50.720
as best you can.

32:53.680 --> 32:55.160
If you made your decision, let me know.

32:57.320 --> 32:58.380
As a doctor.

33:12.670 --> 33:14.300
The order of rescue should be…

33:24.650 --> 33:26.110
A steel shard has penetrated his shoulder.

33:26.110 --> 33:28.340
I don't know if it's touching the spine or not.

33:28.340 --> 33:30.050
Luckily, his vital signs are strong.

33:30.050 --> 33:32.360
Let's give him some broad spectrum antibiotics and take an X-ray.

33:32.360 --> 33:33.220
I know.

33:34.240 --> 33:35.600
You told me over the radio.

33:36.700 --> 33:38.680
I'll take it from here. Go catch your breath.

33:38.680 --> 33:39.920
No. I'll do it.

33:40.330 --> 33:41.970
Is the mobile X-ray ready?

33:42.630 --> 33:43.480
We're out of negatives.

33:43.840 --> 33:45.990
The sterilizer is broken as well. It's chaos.

33:46.190 --> 33:47.990
I know, but we've got to do something.

33:47.990 --> 33:49.720
Please join me. I can't do this alone.

33:50.160 --> 33:50.910
Let's go.

34:00.330 --> 34:01.230
He's under anesthesia.

34:01.420 --> 34:02.780
The patient.

34:04.210 --> 34:06.080
He can’t die here today.

34:08.630 --> 34:09.790
Let's remove the shard.

34:10.350 --> 34:11.650
Quick and precise.

34:12.429 --> 34:18.540
One, two, three!

35:59.340 --> 36:01.040
His vital signs are good.

36:02.010 --> 36:03.070
Good job!

36:03.810 --> 36:04.860
Good job!

36:09.380 --> 36:10.510
Good job!

36:11.610 --> 36:13.110
Ma'am!

36:38.800 --> 36:39.470
Sir!

36:41.410 --> 36:42.350
Thank you for your hard work.

36:43.300 --> 36:45.790
Your shift is over. Go get some rest.

37:19.930 --> 37:22.210
They're rescuing.

37:22.910 --> 37:25.060
Luckily, we don't have too many casualties.

37:25.540 --> 37:27.630
All the soldiers are alive and safe.

37:27.630 --> 37:29.390
Is Lieutenant Yoon okay?

37:29.390 --> 37:31.300
Yes, she's fine.

37:32.030 --> 37:35.410
Captain Yoo back there. I didn’t stop him.

37:35.790 --> 37:39.140
I thought you might be worried, so I asked you to come in.

37:40.560 --> 37:42.590
He's a soldier and that's his job.

37:45.160 --> 37:46.430
It might sound weird.

37:47.540 --> 37:48.870
But with Captain Yoo there,

37:48.870 --> 37:50.450
I feel much relived.

37:54.180 --> 37:56.770
I think very highly of Captain Yoo.

37:58.000 --> 38:00.230
Shi Jin could become a four-star general.

38:00.230 --> 38:01.460
I have a high expectation to him.

38:02.330 --> 38:05.030
I don't know if he's good enough though.

38:05.030 --> 38:07.110
He's a good soldier.

38:07.110 --> 38:09.300
He's got lots of people who follow him.

38:09.300 --> 38:12.740
I guess Shi Jin is blessed with friendly people.

38:16.780 --> 38:17.630
It's a message from the Taebaek Unit.

38:17.630 --> 38:19.090
None of the medical team members

38:19.090 --> 38:20.020
are hurt

38:20.020 --> 38:22.260
and they're working hard to the rescue job.

38:22.460 --> 38:23.630
You don't have to worry about them.

38:26.360 --> 38:28.940
Are you okay, sweetie?

38:29.230 --> 38:30.750
Yes, I'm fine.

38:31.280 --> 38:32.770
I'm just relieved, mother.

38:34.610 --> 38:36.640
When are they coming back?

38:36.640 --> 38:39.210
As soon as the airport opens up there, we'll send a plane.

38:39.540 --> 38:40.340
When will that be?

38:40.340 --> 38:43.740
Let me talk to Chi Hoon first.

38:43.740 --> 38:46.080
I need to hear his voice.

38:46.080 --> 38:48.680
They can't use their mobile phones yet.

38:48.680 --> 38:49.460
We need to

38:49.460 --> 38:51.370
call the army satellite phone.

38:51.370 --> 38:53.500
- I don't think you can... - Hey!

38:53.900 --> 38:55.700
I invested money in that satellite.

38:56.080 --> 38:57.810
Put me through! Now!

39:01.000 --> 39:04.290
Your mother-in-law yelled at Mr. Han.

39:06.560 --> 39:08.740
Actually, this hospital site

39:08.740 --> 39:10.190
belongs to Chi Hoon's parents.

39:12.420 --> 39:15.830
Ma'am, if you need anything, let me know.

39:22.410 --> 39:23.720
How many people died?

39:32.220 --> 39:33.710
Oops.

39:43.400 --> 39:44.690
Is the operation over?

39:44.690 --> 39:46.020
Yes. Just now.

39:49.020 --> 39:50.070
Is he alive?

39:50.610 --> 39:51.990
For now.

39:55.290 --> 39:56.150
Do you...

39:57.280 --> 39:58.350
I don't have a lighter.

40:02.890 --> 40:04.630
Are you okay?

40:12.610 --> 40:15.610
Forget it. I shouldn’t ask.

40:17.120 --> 40:18.120
Give me a cigarette.

40:19.610 --> 40:21.250
You're a doctor. Quit smoking.

40:38.210 --> 40:39.210
Doctor!

40:39.990 --> 40:40.760
Nurse!

40:43.120 --> 40:44.220
Excuse me.

40:46.470 --> 40:47.550
Nurse!

40:56.430 --> 40:59.560
Where's the doctor? I need a doctor.

40:59.560 --> 41:00.620
No.

41:00.620 --> 41:01.540
How dare you?

41:02.220 --> 41:03.240
What's going on?

41:03.530 --> 41:05.700
Ms. Ha, He…

41:06.660 --> 41:08.630
I guess I should talk to you.

41:09.160 --> 41:10.270
You know me, right?

41:10.270 --> 41:13.460
I’m Jin Yeong Su, the general manager of the plant.

41:13.460 --> 41:14.580
So what?

41:15.290 --> 41:18.950
I've been standing around all day. My blood sugar is low.

41:19.940 --> 41:22.430
I feel so very dizzy.

41:22.430 --> 41:26.120
Oh my! I'm exhausted.

41:31.010 --> 41:37.710
Get me some glucose or vitamins. Right here.

41:38.420 --> 41:40.310
With some nutrients.

41:41.150 --> 41:42.430
I said no, but...

41:42.430 --> 41:43.970
I got this. Keep working.

41:48.350 --> 41:49.720
This is Housemother B.

41:49.720 --> 41:53.690
There's a patient who's dying to get glucose or vitamins.

41:53.690 --> 41:56.970
If there's a doctor who's dying of boredom,

41:56.970 --> 41:59.390
come over here and treat him. Over!

41:59.960 --> 42:02.900
Really? What's his condition?

42:03.660 --> 42:05.420
He needs his eyes checked.

42:06.150 --> 42:07.740
If he's not blind, I don't know how he can't see

42:07.740 --> 42:11.020
the patients lying on beds here.

42:11.020 --> 42:13.690
He said he might die of exhaustion.

42:13.690 --> 42:14.910
He can still talk though.

42:14.910 --> 42:17.410
What an idiot!

42:17.890 --> 42:19.020
Bye! Over!

42:21.910 --> 42:23.170
What's your name?

42:23.170 --> 42:26.380
Ha Ja Ae. What's your name?

42:26.380 --> 42:28.280
What did you say?

42:29.320 --> 42:30.660
What? How dare you?

42:30.660 --> 42:31.960
What kind of attitude is that?

42:31.960 --> 42:33.310
You have no respect for us, so I'm treating you the same way.

42:34.080 --> 42:36.500
Okay, I know your name. How old are you?

42:39.270 --> 42:43.930
You! You'll pay for this.

42:43.930 --> 42:47.270
Okay, okay. I'll wait for this.

42:47.770 --> 42:48.920
Ms. Choi, come here.

42:50.470 --> 42:52.390
The sterilizer's broken. We have lots to do.

42:52.390 --> 42:54.150
Ha Ja Ae! Ha Ja Ae!

42:54.560 --> 42:55.850
Get away.

42:55.850 --> 42:57.060
Hey!

43:00.980 --> 43:01.790
What should we do?

43:02.540 --> 43:04.310
We don't have enough food

43:04.310 --> 43:07.250
to feed the medical team members and the injured.

43:09.290 --> 43:11.340
We've just survived a life-and-death situation

43:11.340 --> 43:12.810
and are facing a food crisis.

43:14.430 --> 43:16.680
Let's make do with C-rations...

43:29.570 --> 43:31.330
I figured you'd be starving.

43:43.720 --> 43:49.620
Will this do? I made it enough for 100 persons for now.

43:49.620 --> 43:51.740
Perfect. You're the best.

43:52.440 --> 43:55.460
We’ll buy your drink for 100 persons.

43:57.160 --> 44:00.170
It's on Sergeant Seo.

44:01.640 --> 44:03.100
I received a pay cut.

44:09.350 --> 44:11.710
Squad One, come on out to the cafeteria.

44:25.640 --> 44:27.250
Listen to me while you're eating.

44:27.740 --> 44:28.420
At ease.

44:30.390 --> 44:32.010
You've worked so hard for two days.

44:33.200 --> 44:34.460
Headquarters sent messages

44:34.460 --> 44:35.260
to your parents.

44:35.260 --> 44:36.220
Don’t worry.

44:37.200 --> 44:38.610
As soon as the communication lines are fixed,

44:38.610 --> 44:40.050
we'll let you talk to your parents. ow.

44:40.440 --> 44:41.310
Hang in there.

44:41.950 --> 44:44.580
- Yes, sir. - Yes, sir.

44:46.800 --> 44:48.790
You'll continue this rescue mission tomorrow.

44:49.750 --> 44:53.480
It'll be hard. So as soon as you finish eating, get some sleep.

44:55.410 --> 44:56.470
About what happened today.

44:58.230 --> 44:59.470
and the situation here,

45:00.650 --> 45:02.770
don't think too much and empty your minds.

45:04.050 --> 45:06.990
You just follow my orders.

45:10.420 --> 45:12.520
I'll always make the right decisions for you.

45:14.540 --> 45:15.580
Do you understand?

45:15.580 --> 45:17.920
- Yes, sir! - Yes, sir!

45:19.610 --> 45:20.850
That's all for now.

45:56.580 --> 45:59.820
Did you come here on your own

45:59.820 --> 46:01.440
or on my father's order?

46:04.530 --> 46:07.860
It's the commander's responsibility

46:07.860 --> 46:09.400
to send the best soldiers to the most dangerous places.

46:11.300 --> 46:13.570
I don't understand why you baking uo him.

46:15.030 --> 46:16.890
If you asked me, I'm not happy.

46:16.890 --> 46:18.170
Call your father.

46:18.710 --> 46:20.280
He’s been worried you.

46:24.720 --> 46:26.160
What about you?

46:28.610 --> 46:31.340
How would you have felt if something had happened to me?

46:39.840 --> 46:44.460
I would've regretted every moment

46:44.460 --> 46:45.700
that I ran away from you.

46:50.810 --> 46:52.190
Why are you just standing there?

47:46.260 --> 47:47.020
Move!

47:47.410 --> 47:48.340
It's my job.

47:48.340 --> 47:50.670
I know it's your job. Move.

47:57.280 --> 47:59.670
Without a sterilizer, we have too much to do.

48:00.130 --> 48:01.900
Aren't you scared?

48:02.990 --> 48:04.250
What did I tell you?

48:04.250 --> 48:05.620
We should've gone back

48:05.620 --> 48:06.790
when I asked you to run.

48:07.680 --> 48:08.740
If I had a wife and children,

48:08.740 --> 48:11.060
I could go home.

48:11.060 --> 48:12.830
Why didn't you get married earlier?

48:12.830 --> 48:14.010
Why did you waste your time?

48:14.010 --> 48:15.120
Look who's talking.

48:19.470 --> 48:23.020
Okay. Repeat after me. One-zero-three-zero.

48:23.020 --> 48:25.690
One-zero-three-zero? What's that?

48:25.690 --> 48:27.180
My laptop password.

48:28.120 --> 48:29.590
If I die here,

48:29.590 --> 48:31.600
go to the C drive of my laptop.

48:31.600 --> 48:33.640
Find a folder

48:33.640 --> 48:35.340
called "Bulbul Bird" under "Hospital."

48:35.340 --> 48:37.560
I want you to delete that folder.

48:37.970 --> 48:39.330
Do me a favor as a friend.

48:39.330 --> 48:40.490
What's in there?

48:42.500 --> 48:43.590
Disgusting!

48:44.360 --> 48:45.530
Delete it!

48:45.530 --> 48:47.930
You'll see more than you can imagine.

48:47.930 --> 48:48.850
My god.

48:48.850 --> 48:51.190
I need you to delete it yourself.

48:51.190 --> 48:52.390
You pervert!

48:52.390 --> 48:54.680
One-zero-three-zero? From tens to thirties?

48:54.680 --> 48:56.100
Delete it right now!

48:56.760 --> 48:58.190
Not until I die.

48:58.210 --> 48:59.480
Oh my!

48:59.480 --> 49:00.790
Let’s got check the patients.

49:00.790 --> 49:03.490
Let's turn it off. It's finished.

49:05.600 --> 49:06.820
Delete it!

49:09.730 --> 49:12.480
Eek! So disgusting!

49:15.000 --> 49:15.890
Is he awake?

49:15.890 --> 49:16.800
Not yet.

49:16.800 --> 49:18.620
We have to keep an eye on him until tomorrow.

49:25.220 --> 49:26.710
Is this him?

49:26.710 --> 49:28.180
The one from the yard of the plant?

49:28.560 --> 49:30.480
Yes, he's conscious.

49:37.140 --> 49:40.620
He's getting better. Check his vitals every three hours.

49:44.230 --> 49:45.290
A hard bone fracture.

49:45.680 --> 49:47.170
She's pregnant, so I treated her without anesthesia.

49:47.610 --> 49:49.930
It must be hurt, but she bore that.

49:50.270 --> 49:51.350
The baby is so brave.

49:53.570 --> 49:55.530
Is that your phone?

49:55.830 --> 49:57.390
It's some classical music that I like

49:57.720 --> 49:58.920
to comfort the baby.

50:00.480 --> 50:01.390
You're a true doctor

50:02.040 --> 50:03.020
and a real father now.

50:09.810 --> 50:11.120
He listens to classical music?

50:37.380 --> 50:39.250
Thanks for your shoes.

50:40.310 --> 50:42.140
Thank you.

52:15.510 --> 52:17.070
be careful.

52:29.720 --> 52:30.750
You crazy idiot!

52:30.750 --> 52:32.370
You don't think

52:32.370 --> 52:33.720
I know where you take your naps?

52:33.720 --> 52:36.270
Ouch! Ouch! Can you let go of me?

52:36.270 --> 52:39.620
Dr. Kang. You did a good job today.

53:23.340 --> 53:24.020
Sir!

53:26.220 --> 53:27.040
Do you need anything?

53:28.570 --> 53:30.490
I'm just looking around. Do your job.

53:31.520 --> 53:33.830
Your shoulder... Are you hurt?

53:37.440 --> 53:38.530
Can you take a look at it?

53:38.530 --> 53:39.380
Yes, sir!

53:45.810 --> 53:47.080
It looks pretty bad.

53:47.430 --> 53:48.420
I think you need stitches.

53:49.030 --> 53:51.200
No wonder it hurt so much.

53:52.110 --> 53:52.960
I'll go get a doctor.

53:52.960 --> 53:54.810
Don't bother. I'll go.

53:55.300 --> 53:56.440
Come this way.

54:08.780 --> 54:09.930
What happened?

54:13.770 --> 54:15.150
I was just clumsy.

54:23.170 --> 54:24.350
I'm okay.

54:28.290 --> 54:29.370
Did you hear that?

54:31.030 --> 54:32.600
I asked you using telepathy.

54:34.260 --> 54:36.790
I heard it loud and clear.

54:44.090 --> 54:45.880
I'm glad you're here.

54:47.030 --> 54:48.010
Thank you for

54:51.040 --> 54:52.270
fighting with us.

54:55.280 --> 54:56.650
Thank you.

55:02.720 --> 55:03.800
You too.

55:12.030 --> 55:14.760
I said mean things to you earlier.

55:15.030 --> 55:16.290
I know.

55:19.380 --> 55:20.400
You know?

55:20.400 --> 55:22.530
Do you know how many years I've worked as a doctor?

55:24.540 --> 55:26.740
A doctor with a scalpel

55:27.160 --> 55:29.360
sees more death

55:29.360 --> 55:31.030
than a soldier with a gun.

55:33.830 --> 55:37.480
If I crossed the line,

55:39.330 --> 55:40.560
I'm sorry.

55:42.650 --> 55:45.100
I hope you're okay.

55:46.960 --> 55:48.320
I mean it.

55:56.080 --> 55:59.220
If you want to make me feel better,

55:59.610 --> 56:01.380
do something that you're good at.

56:02.180 --> 56:03.230
Something I'm good at?

56:06.040 --> 56:07.070
What's that?

56:08.350 --> 56:09.560
Silly jokes.

56:10.640 --> 56:14.220
I think I need silly jokes the most at the moment.

56:18.880 --> 56:20.570
You're so pretty.

56:23.230 --> 56:24.600
You can't see me.

56:24.600 --> 56:25.990
I saw you earlier.

56:27.760 --> 56:29.380
You're always pretty.

56:31.980 --> 56:33.480
Don't be serious.

56:33.710 --> 56:35.560
I'm joking.

56:42.870 --> 56:44.370
I missed you a lot.

56:48.420 --> 56:53.580
I couldn't keep you out of my head.

57:01.210 --> 57:02.320
I kept myself busy,

57:04.050 --> 57:05.330
tried to distract myself

57:07.690 --> 57:09.260
and I drank a lot.

57:13.090 --> 57:15.530
But I still missed you a lot.

57:25.250 --> 57:27.020
You didn't expect this?

57:30.950 --> 57:32.080
Think about it.

57:33.780 --> 57:35.680
I meant everything I said.

58:21.350 --> 58:24.280
Next Episode

58:24.840 --> 58:26.440
Do you go all the way

58:27.070 --> 58:28.750
with everything you do?

58:28.750 --> 58:30.600
I'm a thorough man.

58:31.300 --> 58:32.950
I make sure I stay alive

58:32.950 --> 58:34.620
under all circumstances.

58:34.620 --> 58:35.920
How are things inside?

58:35.920 --> 58:37.260
It could collapse at any minute.

58:37.260 --> 58:39.780
Aftershock! Everyone! Get out of here!

58:40.270 --> 58:42.490
I'm sorry.

58:42.490 --> 58:43.840
What's that noise?

58:43.840 --> 58:45.150
Check the power plant!

58:45.700 --> 58:47.130
What's wrong with your hand?

58:47.570 --> 58:50.280
Big Boss! Big Boss! Respond if you can hear this.

58:51.390 --> 58:53.010
I'm ready to the site.

58:53.580 --> 58:54.800
I don't want to trip and fall.

58:54.800 --> 58:56.270
Is anyone there?

58:57.030 --> 58:59.470
Someone's dead!
